title: Coral skeletons left by major earthquake over 630 years ago serve as a warning for Caribbean region
description: An catastrophic earthquake rocked the north eastern Caribbean sometime between 1381 and 1391.
content:

An earthquake exceeding magnitude 8.0 rocked the north eastern Caribbean somet… [+3804 chars]
de: Korallenskelette, die ein schweres Erdbeben vor über 630 Jahren hinterlassen hat, dienen als Warnung für die Karibikregion. Irgendwann zwischen 1381 und 1391 erschütterte ein katastrophales Erdbeben die Nordostkaribik.
en: Coral skeletons left by major earthquake over 630 years ago serve as a warning for Caribbean region. An catastrophic earthquake rocked the north eastern Caribbean sometime between 1381 and 1391.
la: Sceleta corallia maioribus terrae motu super 630 annos relicta sunt ut admonitio regionis Caribbeae sit. Terrae motus calamitosus movebatur ad septentrionem orientalem Caribbean olim inter 1381 et 1391 .

title: Structural barriers control the spatial extent of slow earthquake slip
description: This study shows that slow earthquake slip in the Nankai Trough is confined by structural barriers, including fault geometry, material contrasts, and subducted ridges, revealing key controls on the potential extent of future megathrust ruptures.
content:
• Sugioka, H. et al. Tsunamigenic potential of the shallow subduction plate boundary inferred from slow seismic slip. Nat. Geosci.5, 414418 (2012). Google Scholar 
  • Todd, E. K. et al. Ear… [+14017 chars]
de: Strukturelle Barrieren kontrollieren die räumliche Ausdehnung des langsamen Erdbebenrutschs. Diese Studie zeigt, dass der langsame Erdbebenrutsch im Nankai-Trog durch strukturelle Barrieren, einschließlich Verwerfungsgeometrie, Materialkontraste und subduzierte Grate, begrenzt wird, was wichtige Kontrollen über das potenzielle Ausmaß zukünftiger Megathrust-Brüche offenbart.
en: Structural barriers control the spatial extent of slow earthquake slip. This study shows that slow earthquake slip in the Nankai Trough is confined by structural barriers, including fault geometry, material contrasts, and subducted ridges, revealing key controls on the potential extent of future megathrust ruptures.
la: Claustra structurae ambitus terrae motus lento lapsus coercent. Hoc studium ostendit tardum terrae motus in Nankai Trough lapsus, structuris claustris coarctatum, inclusa geometrica culpa, repugnantia materialia, et iugis subducta, ostendens clavem regiminum in potentia rupta megathrustae futurae.
